==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Malacobdella
<hw>Mal`a*cob*del"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>malako`s</grk> soft + <?/ a leech.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A genus of nemertean worms, parasitic in the gill cavity of clams
and other bivalves. They have a large posterior sucker, like that of a
leech. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Bdellomorpha</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malacoderm</ent>⟦br⟧
